  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension is considered to form a dominant, discordant feature by virtue of its inappropriate siting, design, scale, massing, bulk, form and height which would severely interrupt the existing unaltered roofline on the group of terrace buildings it forms part of. The proposal would therefore clearly fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the designated Grade II Listed building, the wider terrace setting and the New River Conservation Area and would be readily visible from both short and longer views from the surrounding public and private realm. The works would therefore cause harm to the significance of the heritage asset contrary to paragraph 195 of Chapter 16 (conserving and enhancing the historic environment) of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021, policies HC1 and D4 of the London Plan 2021, policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies 2013, guidance contained within Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines 2002 and Islington's Urban Design Guide 2017."
